# Unit Converter — Project Rules

## SSOT

- Requirements: `docs/PRD.md` v0.2
- Traceability: `docs/traceability.md`
- To-Do: `docs/TODO.md`
- Gap: `docs/gap-analysis.md`

## Architecture (SRP)

Package root: `unit_converter/` (lecture SSOT)

- `unit_converter/app/input_parser.py` — parse & validate only
- `unit_converter/domain/unit_registry.py` — register & lookup units (OCP)
- `unit_converter/domain/converter.py` — meter-based conversion only
- `unit_converter/app/output_formatter.py` — json | csv | table output only
- `unit_converter/infrastructure/config_loader.py` — JSON/YAML load only
- `unit_converter/cli.py` — orchestration only
- `tests/test_converter.py` · `tests/test_cli.py` — project root (Dual-Track)

## Conversion constants (meter = 1.0)

- feet: 3.28084
- yard: 1.09361
- Display: round to 4 decimal places

## Error messages (exact strings)

- E-FMT: `Invalid format. Use unit:value (ex: meter:2.5)`
- E-NUM: `Invalid number: {value_str}`
- E-NEG: `Negative value not allowed`
- E-UNIT: `Unknown unit: {unit}`

## TDD / ARRR

- Ask = RED, Respond = GREEN, Refine = REFACTOR
- RED: no production implementation; tests must FAIL
- `pytest.fail("RED: [ID]")` allowed in skeleton; no skip/xfail
- 1 RED bundle = 1 commit
- Dual-Track: `tests/test_cli.py` (A), `tests/test_converter.py` (B)

## OCP

- New unit = register in registry or config; do not modify converter core logic

## Python

- Python 3.10+
- pytest for all tests
